HEADWORD: Prickmadam
<hw>Prick"mad`am</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>trique-madame</ets>. Cf. <er>Tripmadam</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name given to several species of stonecrop,
used as ingredients of vermifuge medicines. See
<er>Stonecrop</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

